cs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**FieldError** (optional) — Rendered when `errorMessage` is provided. Rendered below the Group, above the description. Associated with the field for accessibility."},"158":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-26","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"**Text** (optional) — Description block rendered when `description` is provided."},"159":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-27","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#internal-structure","content":"Children you pass to FieldFrame (e.g. `Input`, `Button`, `DateInput`, `SelectValue`) are rendered inside the Group. The provider ensures nested Input and Button read the same disabled/required state as the frame."},"160":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-28","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#states","content":"The states **disabled**, **readonly**, and **invalid** are applied when the field wrapper (e.g. TextField, NumberField, Select) is marked as disabled, readonly, or invalid respectively. The frame reflects these and other states via data attributes on the group."},"161":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-29","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#states","content":"State"},"162":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-30","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#states","content":"CSS Selector"},"163":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-31","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/field-frame#states","content":"disabled — Applied when the field wrapper is disabled."},"164":{"id":"/docs/components/field-frame-32","page_id":"/docs/components/field-frame","tags":[],"type":"text","url